A N A C T
RELATING TO STATE AFFAIRS AND GOVERNMENT -- STATE-OWNED AND
OPERATED PRINTING FACILITIES PREFERENCE ACT
Introduced By: Senators Sosnowski, DiMario, and DiPalma
Date Introduced: March 07, 2025
Referred To: Senate Finance
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Title 42 of the General Laws entitled "STATE AFFAIRS AND
2 GOVERNMENT" is hereby amended by adding thereto the following chapter:
3 CHAPTER 167
4 STATE-OWNED AND OPERATED PRINTING FACILITIES PREFERENCE ACT
5 42-167-1. Short title.
6 This chapter shall be known and may be cited as “State-Owned and Operated Printing
7 Facilities Preference”.
8 42-167-2. Use of state-owned/operated printing facilities.
9 Any state agency, state institution of higher education, and quasi-public agency which
10 engages in the printing of more than fifty (50) copies of a contract, publication, brochure, mail
11 piece, notice, and/or promotional material shall, when practicable, use an existing state-
12 owned/operated print shop/facility as long as said state-owned/operated print shop/facility is
13 capable of processing and manufacturing the aforementioned materials.
14 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
