EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO STATE AFFAIRS AND GOVERNMENT -- STATE-OWNED AND
OPERATED PRINTING FACILITIES PREFERENCE ACT
***
1 This act would require, that any state agency, state institution of higher education, and
2 quasi-public agency that engages in printing more than fifty (50) copies of a contract, publication,
3 brochure, notice, or promotional material to use a state-owned or operated print shop capable of
4 processing the material whenever such use is practicable.
5 This act would take effect upon passage.
